Peter Marais, Freedom Front Plus’ (FF+) candidate for Western Cape Premier, says he wants to be deployed to the National Assembly to go toe-to-toe with the Economic Freedom Fighters (EFF) and the Democratic Alliance (DA). The FF+ won just 1.57% of the vote in the Western Cape and should be allocated at least one seat in the provincial legislature. But the 70-year-old career politician says his talents would be wasted in the backbenches of the legislature. “I would love to cross swords with the EFF.
